  "prompt": "How common is dying in your sleep?",
  "response": "The phenomenon of dying in one's sleep is relatively uncommon, but it does happen, particularly amongst older adults or individuals with certain health conditions. Dying in one's sleep can be attributed to various factors, including cardiac arrhythmias, heart attacks, strokes, or respiratory issues like sleep apnea.\n\nThe prevalence of dying in sleep varies based on age group and overall health status. Generally, the risk increases as people age and develop chronic health issues. Preventative healthcare, regular check-ups, and addressing underlying health conditions can reduce the risk.\n\nIt's essential to consult healthcare professionals for personalized advice and to mitigate any concerns related to sleep and overall health.",
